

GOALS

  everything in doubles
  not-a-number (NAN) supported
  addition and subtraction supported  (FUTURE)
  datetime supported as a unixtime (seconds since epoch) or SQL format
  "now" (this second) supported



PLACES

  <axis> clip-min, clip-max, and snap-to attributes
  <grid> x-modulus, y-modulus, x-offset, and y-offset attributes
  <label> modulus, offset, and template attributes
  <mysql> data returned from database   (datetime especially useful)
  <rpn> calculations
  <textfile> data in file



DECIMAL POWERS

  Y   yotta       1e24       Greek or Latin octo, "eight"
  Z   zetta       1e21       Latin septem, "seven"
  E   exa         1e18       Greek hex, "six"
  P   peta        1e15       Greek pente, "five"
  T   tera        1e12       Greek teras, "monster"
  G   giga        1e9        Greek gigas, "giant"
  M   mega        1e6        Greek megas, "large"
  k   kilo        1e3        Greek chilioi, "thousand"
  h   hecto       1e2        Greek hekaton, "hundred"
  D   deca        1e1        Greek deka, "ten"

  #   just the number (most useful with <label> templates)

  d   deci        1e-1       Latin decimus, "tenth"
  c   centi       1e-2       Latin centum, "hundred"
  m   milli       1e-3       Latin mille, "thousand"
  u   micro       1e-6       Latin micro or Greek mikros, "small"
  n   nano        1e-9       Latin nanus or Greek nanos, "dwarf"
  p   pico        1e-12      Spanish pico, "a bit"
  f   femto       1e-15      Danish-Norwegian femten, "fifteen"
  a   atto        1e-18      Danish-Norwegian atten, "eighteen"
  z   zepto       1e-21      Latin septem, "seven"
  y   yocto       1e-24      Greek or Latin octo, "eight"



BINARY POWERS

  modifier:  b

  bY  yottabytes  1024^8
  bZ  zettabytes  1024^7
  bE  exabytes    1024^6
  bP  petabytes   1024^5
  bT  terabytes   1024^4
  bG  gigabytes   1024^3
  bM  megabytes   1024^2
  bk  kilobytes   1024



DATETIME POWERS

  modifier:  d

  (these reflect common unix character-names for the date parts (see strftime))

  dY   Year
  dM   Month
  dO   mOnth    (prints abbreviated month name in <label> templates)
  dW   Week     (prints abbreviated day of week in <label> templates)
  dD   Day
  dH   Hour
  dI   mInute
  dS   Second

  dN   now




